<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Culture characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Cultures incubated on PDA at 25 °C in darkness. Colony flat with white felty aerial mycelium, turning white to dark brown aerial mycelium, conidiomata irregularly distributed on the agar surface.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Additional specimens examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
CHINA. Heilongjiang Province: Yichun city, on symptomatic branches of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula albo-sinensis" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albo-sinensis">Betula albo-sinensis</taxonomicName>
, 27 July 2016, Q. Yang, living culture CFCC 52560 (BJFC-S1473); on symptomatic branches of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Betula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Betula costata" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="costata">Betula costata</taxonomicName>
